 b) Aim: JQuery selectors,JQuery hide and show effects i) JQuery selectors: using ID selector: code: <!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head>  <script type="text/javascript" src="D:\69012\ngt\jq.js"></script> <script> $(document).ready(function(){ $("button").click(function(){ $("#test").hide(); }); }); </script> </head> <body> <h2>program for ID selector</h2> <p>Good Morning</p> <p id="test">Good Afternoon</p> <button>Click here</button> </body> </html> Output: Before: 
 
After: 
 
 
 
 
 
Using class selector: Code: <!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head>  <script type="text/javascript" src="D:\69012\ngt\jq.js"></script> <script> $(document).ready(function(){ $("button").click(function(){ $(".test").hide(); }); }); </script> </head> <body> <h2>program for class selector</h2> <p>Good Morning</p> <p class="test">Good Evening</p> <button>Click here</button> </body> </html> Output: Before: 
 
After: 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
ii)Jquery hide and show effects: Code: <!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head>  <script type="text/javascript" src="D:\69012\ngt\jq.js"></script> <script> $(document).ready(function(){ $("#hide").click(function(){ $("p").hide(); }); $("#show").click(function(){ $("p").show(); }); }); </script> </head> <body> <p>If you click on the "Hide" button,I will disappear..</p> <button id="hide">Hide</button> <button id="show">Show</button> </body> </html> 
 
Output: 
 
After clicking on hide button 
 
After clicking on show button 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
c)Aim: JQuery fading effects and JQuery sliding effects: i)JQuery fading effects: code: <!DOCTYPE html> <html><head> <script type="text/javascript" src="D:\69012\ngt\jq.js"></script> <script> $(document).ready(function(){ $("#button1").click(function(){ $("#div1").fadeIn(); $("#div2").fadeIn("slow"); $("#div3").fadeIn(3000); }); $("#button2").click(function(){ $("#div1").fadeOut(); $("#div2").fadeOut("slow"); $("#div3").fadeOut(3000); }); }); </script> </head> <body> <p>Demolnstrate fadeOut() with different parameters</p> <button id=button1>Click to fade in boxes</button> <button id=button2>Click to fade out boxes</button><br><br> <div id="div1" style="width:80px;height:80px;display:none;backgroundcolor:red;"></div><br> <div id="div2" style="width:80px;height:80px;display:none;backgroundcolor:blue;"></div><br> <div id="div3" style="width:80px;height:80px;display:none;backgroundcolor:yellow;"></div><br> </body> </html> 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Output: 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
