v) Slide Up: Code: <!DOCTYPE html> <html> <head> <script type="text/javascript" src="D:\69012\ngt\jq.js"></script> <script> $(document).ready(function(){ $("#button1").click(function(){ $("#div1").slideDown("slow"); $("#div2").slideDown("slow"); $("#div3").slideDown("slow"); }); $("#button2").click(function(){ $("#div1").slideUp("slow"); $("#div2").slideUp("slow"); $("#div3").slideUp("slow"); }); }); </script> </head> <body> <p>Demonstrate slideUp() and slideDown() with different parameters</p> <button id=button1>Click to slide down boxes</button> <button id=button2>Click to slide up boxes</button> <div id="div1" style="width:80px;height:80px;display:none;backgroundcolor:red;"></div><br> <div id="div2" style="width:80px;height:80px;display:none;backgroundcolor:blue;"></div><br> <div id="div3" style="width:80px;height:80px;display:none;backgroundcolor:yellow;"></div><br> </body> </html>
